results.title: A Nerd of the Day  What Have  I Dumb Advice from Dear Crabby
results.description:
What Have I Dumb?
(A Couple of Do’s and A Lot of Don’ts I’ve Learned in Life)

I think we’ve all said or did some things that we regret sooner or later.  I learned quickly that words and/or actions can be powerful.  Words can heal.  They can make one laugh…cry…show gratitude…convey Love at many different levels in any relationship.  The combination of a group of words we choose can unlock the truth or temporary cloak something…that eventually results in a “Back at You” moment.

In this cyberspace communicating days, words and actions have caused some serious damage to others who don’t realize it now that it’s better to think before you speak or do moment.

So…here is a list of things that have resulted in questioning, “What have I dumb?”
If you don't have the $$ to pay for this word document, here it is below:

1.	 When riding an elevator and there is a large woman standing across from you, and you ask, “When is your baby due?” and her response is, “I’m Not pregnant”…Exit the elevator as soon as possible.

2.	 Don’t microwave a pack of frozen fish sticks at lunchtime inside a large clerical office kitchen.

3.	Don’t run a 5 mile marathon wearing a loose sanitary napkin.

4.	Don’t ever light a cigarette with a Bunsen burner…unless you want to have your eyelashes and eye brows burned to a crisp.

5.	Never apply bleach to your laundry containing all of your colorful work clothes.

6.	Don’t spit in the wind.

7.	It’s never a good time to invite your new best friend to dinner the same time a family member is using the restroom.  Dinner may be roast beef…but when your friend arrives and says, “Ahh…we’re having chili dogs…Yumm!!!” …to later find out that your family member that was in the restroom had a couple of chili dogs for lunch.

8.	If you’ve never driven a large motorcycle before, make sure you know how to operate the brakes before driving off…otherwise you’ll crash into a group of filled garbage cans.

9.	If you want to keep all of your fingers intact, hand your puppies tasty chicken with your hand “cupped”…not holding the piece with 2 fingers.

10.	When…in the middle of the night…you return from using the restroom and attempt to sit at the edge of your bed…only to flip over and fall flat on your butt…turn the lights on first.

11.	Don’t eat an entire can of cooked corn just before going to bed…only to wake up with severe stomach pains and a trip to the emergency room.

12.	Do learn how to operate a mobility scooter…outside…before trying to drive it into the house with the front door closed.  Also, make sure not to detach the outside water faucets.

13.	If you happen to travel to a casino after eating a large bowl of Texas chili…make sure to get a hotel room rather than trying to save money by sleeping in a small car at the casino parking lot….with all the windows closed.

14.	Keep your mouth closed when riding a bicycle so not to crunch on a fly(s)…not a good bite-size taste tester.

15.	If you’re first job as a prep-cook at a popular Mexican restaurant…and never used a sharp knife before…make sure you remove the 10 bloody bandages from your fingers before making/mixing a large tub of potato salad. …that way the patrons will not be disgustingly surprised when they bite into their salad.

16.	When exiting the restroom, make sure you don’t have a toilet paper trail (stuck to your sweatpants) when walking back to the living room filled with company.

                                                                                                                                                                          ©Esther Monsalve
The Angel Shop

Support Operation Smile
